giuseppe chiara ( 1602 – 24 august 1685 ) was an italian jesuit missionary active in 17th century japan . he entered japan at a time when christianity was strictly forbidden in an attempt to locate fellow priest cristóvão ferreira who had apostatized his christian faith at the hands of torture by the japanese authorities in 1633 . chiara was also tortured and eventually became an apostate as well . he later married a japanese woman , taking the name and samurai status of her late husband , okamoto san 'em on ( japanese : 岡本三右衛門 ) , and would live in japan until his death in 1685 .